 is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"In order to further their research, the team wanted to determine whether the birds’ preference for large feet is a learned behavior or an instinctive one so the researchers conducted an experiment in which some blue-footed boobies were raised in captivity and then released into the wild.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice D is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
